<FIRST>u a AM-PlaneDown     07-11 0132</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Plane Down,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Small Plane Crashes near Residential Neighborhood</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A single-engine plane sturck power lines
and crashed early Tuesday near a residential neighborhood,
authorities said.
   Police said they were told the plane had taken off from Arlington
Airport and crashed about 2 a.m. south of Interstate 20.
   The fate of the plane's occupant was not immediately known.
   An Arlington Fire Department crew was sent to the crash site.
   ``At this point, officers are still checking to see whether the
plane hit any houses,'' said Officer Desmond Freeman. ``We still
don't have much information from the scene.''
   Freeman said the plane struck power lines.
   ``There were reports of the plane being flown erratically over
parts of the city,'' he said. ``That is what brought our attention
to it.''
</TEXT>
