<FIRST>d a PM-CaliforniaEarthquake     07-11 0151</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-California Earthquake,0156</SECOND>
<HEAD>Moderate Earthquake Shakes Bishop Area</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BISHOP, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A moderate earthquake shook several
Northern California communities, but no damage was reported.
   The tremor, which measured 4.5 on the Richter scale, struck at
9:15 p.m. Monday and was centered about 10 miles west of Bishop, the
U.S. Geological Society said.
   ``It rolled,'' said Pam Galvin of the Bishop Police Department.
``I was standing up doing some work and I felt the ground roll under
me. It was really bizarre. I've never felt one like that before.''
   It also was felt 120 miles to the west in Fresno and in Mammouth
Lakes.
   The Richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on
seismographs. Every increase of one number means a tenfold increase
in magnitude.
   An earthquake of 3.5 on the Richter scale can cause slight damage
in the local area, 4 moderate damage, 5 considerable damage.
</TEXT>
