<HEAD>Ethiopian Rebels Claim 480 Coup Participants Slain</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 4th graf, ``In a ...'' to CORRECT name of Ethiopian president
to Mariam. Pickup last, ``Eritrean rebels ...''</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rebels claim the Ethiopian government has
rounded up and executed more than 480 alleged participants in an
attempted coup in May.
   In a clandestine radio broadcast, the Eritrean People's
Liberation Front also said 230 other people, mostly soldiers, had
been imprisoned for taking part in the failed coup.
   The broadcast, monitored in Nairobi on Monday night, said 40 of
those killed had been high-ranking officers of Ethiopia's 2nd Army,
based in northern Eritrea Province.
   In a news conference in Addis Ababa last month, President
Mengistu Haile Mariam said about 190 officers and soldiers had been
either killed or imprisoned during and after the coup.
   Eritrean rebels have been fighting for more than a
quarter-century for a separate homeland.
