<HEAD>Pope Names New Bishops For Michigan, Louisiana</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II today named Monsignor
Robert John Rose to be bishop of Grand Rapids, Mich., and appointed
the Rev. Sam Jacobs bishop of Alexandria, La.
   The Vatican said Rose, currently bishop of Gaylord, Mich., will
replace Bishop Joseph Matthew Breitenbeck, who has retired.
   Rose, 59, was born in Grand Rapids. He was ordained in 1955 and
consecrated a bishop in 1981.
   Jacobs, 51, was born in Greenwood, Miss., and was ordained a
priest in 1964 in Lafayette, La. The former Alexandria bishop, John
C. Favolara, has become bishop of St. Petersburg, Fla.
