<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Texas is SO BIG ... well, it's big enough
that language differences have developed in different parts.
   Just like tourists from up North who can't decipher a Texan
twang, sometimes even fellow Texans can't understand each other.
   During debate in the state Senate, a lawmaker from western Texas
happened to use the word ``ostriches.''
   A colleague from southern Texas, Carlos Truan, appeared puzzled
and interrupted.
   Truan, from Corpus Christi, said: ``I thought you said oysters.''
   ``You know how we talk out West,'' said Bill Sims of San Angelo.
