<FIRST>r w AM-US-IsraelTerror     07-11 0203</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-US-Israel Terror,180</SECOND>
<HEAD>State Department Calls Attack on Israeli Bus a Terrorist Act</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A State Department spokesman on Tuesday called
last week's attack on an Israeli bus a terrorist act.
   ``We've seen reports that the Islamic Jihad of Palestine has
publicly claimed responsibility, '' Richard Boucher told reporters.
   ``There are also other reports concerning the motivation of the
individual. It just seems clear that it was a terrorist attack based
on the information we have now.''
   The Israeli government had complained that the U.S. government
did not come out strongly on the incident. It occurred Friday when
an Arab seized the wheel of a bus between Tel Aviv and Jerusalem and
forced it to plunge into a ravine. There were 14 killed, including
two Canadians.
   Boucher said he did not know who was responsible, pointing out
that the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) had called it a
tragedy. He added that he did not have a single definition of a
terrorist act that would cover all possible events.
   Boucher commented as the Anti-Defamation League of B'nai B'rith
released a letter to Secretary of State James Baker complaining that
the department had not condemned the bus attack, but ``merely
expressed sorrow.''
</TEXT>
