<FIRST>r i AM-Germany-Aquino     07-11 0183</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Germany-Aquino,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>West Germany Promises Philippines $58 Mllion in Aid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   West Germany Tuesday promised the
Philippines the equivalent of $58.8 million in development aid this
year, officials said.
   Juergen Warnke, Minister for Economic Development Aid, told
visiting President Corazon Aquino that $21.3 million will go toward
environment and reforestation projects in the Philippines. It was
not immediately clear whether he specified what the remaining money
should be used for.
   Mrs. Aquino is on a week-long, three-nation European visit to
drum up economic aid for the Philippines, which is plagued by a
faltering economy and a $29 billion foreign debt.
   West German leaders have told Mrs. Aquino since her arrival on
Sunday that there is interest in improving bilateral trade and
expanding investment in the Philippines.
   On Monday, West German President Richard von Weizsaecker told
Mrs. Aquino that ties between the Philippines and West Germany would
be strengthened as a result of her trip.
   On Tuesday, Mrs. Aquino met with Chancellor Helmut Kohl before
leaving for Paris.
   Belgium will be Mrs. Aquino's final stop on her European tour.
</TEXT>
